WEBVTT

00:17.760 --> 00:19.751
[radio stations changing]

00:24.770 --> 00:28.513
[Junior Walker &amp; The All Stars' "Shotgun"
playing on radio]

00:28.610 --> 00:30.396
[Buddy laughing]

00:30.480 --> 00:33.938
Oh, man. Now this takes me way back.

00:41.700 --> 00:45.579
Hey, what? You're choking the lifeout
of the steering wheel.

00:46.750 --> 00:48.832
Come on. We got the job done.

00:49.920 --> 00:51.126
Let's enjoy it.

00:54.130 --> 00:55.540
[coughing]

00:57.470 --> 00:59.347
[clears throat] Ow!

00:59.430 --> 01:00.886
-You okay?
-[grunts]

01:01.510 --> 01:02.511
Yeah.

01:03.270 --> 01:04.919
-Buddy, you all right?
-[coughs]

01:06.190 --> 01:07.680
You sure you're okay?

01:07.770 --> 01:08.850
[grunts]

01:09.310 --> 01:10.311
Never better.

01:11.070 --> 01:13.607
Whoa! [chuckling]

01:17.200 --> 01:18.349
You know, I...

01:20.580 --> 01:22.400
I saw these guys

01:22.490 --> 01:28.827
at the Fox Theater, in Detroit, in '65.

01:28.920 --> 01:30.160
[both chuckle]

01:32.050 --> 01:35.122
-God damn, that was some show.
-Hmm.

01:35.920 --> 01:36.921
[exhales]

01:37.010 --> 01:40.138
Do you miss it? Your life back in Detroit?

01:41.100 --> 01:43.170
-[Buddy grunts] Sometimes.
-Hmm.

01:43.810 --> 01:47.473
You know, that city was in its prime.

01:48.770 --> 01:52.809
It was vibrant. And it really had soul.

01:52.900 --> 01:53.935
[Wendy] Hmm.

01:55.820 --> 01:57.526
Yeah, I always thought I...

01:58.530 --> 02:00.361
I'd make my way back.

02:04.790 --> 02:05.779
[Buddy] Yeah.

02:08.750 --> 02:10.877
[exhales]

02:12.380 --> 02:13.699
Promise me,

02:14.880 --> 02:17.371
when you get that casino up and running,

02:18.760 --> 02:21.137
you're gonna get the hell out of here.

02:23.350 --> 02:24.556
Yes?

02:26.560 --> 02:27.879
We have a plan.

02:32.400 --> 02:34.561
There's a small town in Australia.

02:35.440 --> 02:37.897
It's about an hour's drive
from the Gold Coast.

02:39.320 --> 02:40.730
Mullumbimby.

02:45.080 --> 02:46.570
[laughs]

02:47.330 --> 02:48.319
[chuckles] What? Mullum what?

02:50.790 --> 02:51.996
[chuckling]

02:52.080 --> 02:54.412
-Mullumbimby.
-Don't make me laugh.

02:54.500 --> 02:56.297
[laughing]

02:56.380 --> 02:59.417
-Have you been there?
-No. Oh, God, no.

03:00.220 --> 03:01.790
No, I've only read about it.

03:04.600 --> 03:06.966
Growing up,
we didn't have any money to travel.

03:07.060 --> 03:08.596
I mean, we didn't have any money
to do anything,

03:08.680 --> 03:10.386
so I would go to the library.

03:11.310 --> 03:13.301
And I'd put my finger on the map.

03:15.110 --> 03:16.316
[chuckles]

03:17.190 --> 03:18.521
Well, what's it like?

03:19.900 --> 03:20.889
Remote.

03:21.740 --> 03:25.699
Lush. It's surrounded by mountains.
It's near the water.

03:25.780 --> 03:29.159
I mean, it's a lot like the Ozarks.
[laughs]

03:29.250 --> 03:31.070
Except people talk funny there.

03:31.710 --> 03:33.280
I told Marty about it.

03:35.790 --> 03:38.088
At first, it was the name that we liked.

03:40.590 --> 03:41.921
Gold Coast.

03:45.010 --> 03:49.265
And then I remembered this spot nearby,
kind of like a hideout.

03:49.770 --> 03:50.759
Of course, Marty,

03:50.850 --> 03:53.978
he's paranoid that there's gonna be
a tsunami that hits the coast.

03:54.060 --> 03:57.018
But, you know,
I figure the town is so far inland,

03:57.110 --> 04:00.147
I mean, we'll have beach-front property
by the time the water gets to us.

04:00.240 --> 04:02.777
[chuckles]

04:15.500 --> 04:16.489
Buddy. Buddy?

04:28.680 --> 04:29.920
[exclaims]

04:45.990 --> 04:47.526
[exhales]

05:02.210 --> 05:03.199
[knocking on door]

05:05.930 --> 05:06.999
Ruth?

05:09.300 --> 05:10.631
You okay in there?

05:14.140 --> 05:16.096
-Ruth?
-[knocking continues]

05:17.310 --> 05:18.720
[cell phone vibrating]

05:19.400 --> 05:21.436
-Ruth.
-[sniffles]

05:24.740 --> 05:25.729
[knock on door]

05:25.820 --> 05:26.696
What?

05:27.240 --> 05:30.698
[Wyatt] Uncle Cade told me what happened.
I just wanted to see if you were okay.

05:30.780 --> 05:34.989
I'm fine. Just stop being a stalker
and get your shit together for school.

05:35.080 --> 05:36.957
I'm not leaving until you come out.

05:44.130 --> 05:45.370
Suit yourself.

06:10.030 --> 06:10.985
[shudders]

06:17.460 --> 06:19.576
[sobbing]

06:56.620 --> 06:59.202
Buddy told me he wanted to die
at home in his bed.

07:00.670 --> 07:02.661
Do you think he'd be upset
that he died in his car?

07:02.750 --> 07:05.287
No, sweetheart, I don't think
he'd be upset about that.

07:13.470 --> 07:15.381
What were you guys doing out so late?

07:17.310 --> 07:19.471
And why did he smell like gasoline?

07:22.230 --> 07:24.642
Well, Buddy wanted to help us
with something,

07:24.730 --> 07:28.518
_ _ but it was... _
It was Just too much for hIm.

07:29.030 --> 07:30.179
Help us with what?

07:31.200 --> 07:32.986
Why did you let him go with you?

07:35.870 --> 07:37.326
I thought he was better.

07:41.120 --> 07:46.160
It's nobody's fault, Jonah, okay?
Buddy was sick. This was his time.

07:47.960 --> 07:49.040
-All set.
-Yeah.

07:49.130 --> 07:51.121
Thank you, Harry.
Sorry for the short notice.

07:51.220 --> 07:52.335
[Harry sighs] That's life.

07:52.970 --> 07:54.460
Sorry again for your loss.

07:59.180 --> 08:01.262
Why don't we all stay at home today?

08:02.060 --> 08:04.972
Just the four of us? We can...
We can make pancakes.

08:05.560 --> 08:07.357
You okay, Charlotte?
Does that sound like a good idea?

08:08.690 --> 08:11.067
[sighs] I just feel so stupid.

08:11.150 --> 08:13.732
I know that this was coming,
but it just doesn't make...

08:14.490 --> 08:15.650
[Marty] I know.

08:17.870 --> 08:20.111
-I know.
-[Charlotte exhales]

08:20.200 --> 08:21.246
Go help Jonah.

08:25.670 --> 08:26.785
Um...

08:27.960 --> 08:29.700
I'm gonna go try to get in front of this.

08:31.880 --> 08:33.461
At least take the morning.

08:34.840 --> 08:38.253
You blew up their ﬁeld, Wendy.
It's just gonna get worse from here.

08:39.310 --> 08:41.596
Try to stay off the phone.
The feds might be listening.

08:50.360 --> 08:52.180
[chattering]

08:58.950 --> 09:02.158
Any of those dogs
so much as pisses in that barn,

09:02.250 --> 09:03.569
you'll be hearing from our lawyer.

09:03.660 --> 09:05.912
What exactly do you expect to turn up?

09:06.500 --> 09:08.661
His name is Camino Del Rio.

09:09.500 --> 09:10.706
Ring any bells?

09:14.720 --> 09:15.926
He a Mexican?

09:16.510 --> 09:18.922
[Petty] Last he was seen,
he was headed on to your property.

09:21.390 --> 09:24.052
Well, anything you can tell me
about the fire out here last night?

09:24.930 --> 09:28.093
That was a prescribed burn
on one of our fields.

09:28.190 --> 09:30.567
-[Petty] A prescribed burn?
-Mm-hmm.

09:30.650 --> 09:32.527
If you farmed, you'd know.

09:33.820 --> 09:35.185
In the middle of the night?

09:36.320 --> 09:37.856
Because I think you're hiding something.

09:37.950 --> 09:40.236
I think you're trying
to destroy evidence out here.

09:40.320 --> 09:41.571
Evidence of what?

09:42.990 --> 09:44.366
I guess we'll see.

09:53.880 --> 09:56.587
-You okay?
-Stil| walking on two feet, ain't I?

09:58.130 --> 10:01.008
You're late.
And if I find out you're skipping class,

10:01.100 --> 10:02.306
I will hunt you down,

10:02.390 --> 10:05.268
tie you to the back of the beast
and drag you there myself.

10:05.930 --> 10:07.807
Go get Three and get in the damn car.

10:09.020 --> 10:09.896
Go!

10:11.860 --> 10:13.009
Where are you heading?

10:14.440 --> 10:15.350
Work.

10:16.690 --> 10:17.941
Here. Let me see.

10:21.160 --> 10:22.320
Good girl.

10:23.160 --> 10:26.197
Now, you know better than
to let those fuckers get you down.

10:26.660 --> 10:28.366
You play that long game.

10:28.960 --> 10:31.326
You strike back when they least expect it.

10:35.460 --> 10:37.542
We'll get that money, one way or another.

10:48.310 --> 10:49.129
[dogs barking]

10:49.230 --> 10:50.845
-[man] Get over here.
-[woman] There you go.

11:08.000 --> 11:09.786
[cell phone ringing]

11:10.670 --> 11:11.864
Petty.

11:14.540 --> 11:15.700
Copy that.

11:28.640 --> 11:30.301
Can I help you with something?

11:31.560 --> 11:35.519
-Just here to see my business partners.
-And what business is that exactly?

11:36.150 --> 11:38.220
We have a bid for a casino.

11:38.730 --> 11:39.776
Right.

11:39.860 --> 11:43.853
Well, I'm afraid I can't allow you
to have any contact with your partners,

11:43.950 --> 11:47.784
because anything we turn up today could
persuade them to testify against you.

11:48.490 --> 11:51.402
Any contact you have with them
could compromise that.

11:53.370 --> 11:54.997
So, I'm sure you understand.

11:56.840 --> 11:58.296
He's gonna back up.

11:59.840 --> 12:00.659
Asshole.

12:01.340 --> 12:02.250
Pnck.

12:08.850 --> 12:12.172
[man] Simmer down. Simmer down! Good boy.

12:17.690 --> 12:19.317
[sniffs]

12:20.280 --> 12:22.441
Hey! I think we got something.

12:53.390 --> 12:54.880
[Wendy]
Do we know what’s on the warrant?

12:55.560 --> 12:56.720
No, we don't.

12:56.810 --> 12:58.892
It's weird, you know.
Petty didn't actually tell me.

12:59.400 --> 13:01.777
Well, it's a good thing
that we burned that field, at least.

13:01.860 --> 13:04.488
It's not. It's not so good
that you didn't run it by me.

13:05.910 --> 13:08.060
When were we supposed
to talk about it, Marty? Hmm?

13:08.160 --> 13:11.072
When Ruth was being tortured by the cartel
and you were tied up on the ground?

13:11.160 --> 13:13.037
It's not like I stole your credit card
and I bought a dress.

13:13.120 --> 13:14.326
You made the right call. It's just...

13:14.410 --> 13:17.072
we gotta stay on the same page always,
or things fall apart.

13:18.040 --> 13:20.873
You know, you got a real way
of complimenting me

13:20.960 --> 13:23.508
and walking it back in the same breath.
You know that?

13:23.590 --> 13:24.750
Tell me they cleaned out the barn.

13:24.840 --> 13:27.468
Tell me that the feds are not about
to find a herom processmg...

13:28.090 --> 13:29.170
Hey there, Harry.

13:29.760 --> 13:31.591
I'm sorry. Am I interrupting?

13:31.680 --> 13:32.556
No, you're not. No.

13:36.980 --> 13:39.767
This one comes in gray or pink granite.

13:39.860 --> 13:42.010
-It's modern, but timeless.
-Mm-hmm.

13:42.110 --> 13:44.237
You're thinking single occupancy
or double?

13:44.320 --> 13:46.732
[Wendy] Oh, double.
Let's give him some room in there.

13:47.990 --> 13:50.276
-We're getting Buddy a mausoleum?
-Mm-hmm.

13:50.370 --> 13:52.577
-When were you gonna tell me about that?
-I'm telling you now.

13:55.620 --> 13:57.451
[Harry] How do we feel about statues?

17:32.760 --> 17:34.204
I've been texting.

17:34.300 --> 17:35.915
[Wendy] I've been away from my phone.

17:36.010 --> 17:39.594
-It's important.
-I've had something more important.

17:40.300 --> 17:42.131
FBI wants to question me.

17:42.220 --> 17:44.427
An Agent Petty. I'm guessing you know him.

17:45.680 --> 17:47.341
I need to know
what I'm involved with here.

17:47.440 --> 17:49.396
I think you know exactly
what you're involved in.

17:49.480 --> 17:50.356
Do I?

17:51.940 --> 17:53.521
If we're gonna have
any kind of relationship,

17:53.610 --> 17:55.987
you need to start being 100% honest
with me.

17:56.570 --> 17:58.526
The casino deal is completely legal.

17:58.610 --> 18:00.908
But the business your investors
are involved in isn't.

18:04.870 --> 18:05.780
No.

18:08.670 --> 18:10.786
Did you know this
before you started working with them?

18:14.090 --> 18:15.205
Yes.

18:16.920 --> 18:19.297
Well, don't stop now, Charles. Let's go.

18:19.380 --> 18:21.041
You want the whole truth,
now's your chance.

18:30.480 --> 18:32.016
Shit. Fuck.

18:35.320 --> 18:36.230
Hi.

18:38.240 --> 18:39.195
Hi.

18:40.660 --> 18:44.369
I didn't, uh... I didn't know
if you'd be in today.

18:44.450 --> 18:45.610
[chuckles softly]

18:46.500 --> 18:49.867
You think those poles
wipe themselves off? [sniffs]

18:52.040 --> 18:55.248
No, I mean...
You know, you weren't answering my calls.

18:55.340 --> 19:01.256
And, you know, I just figured that I would
make the rounds myself until you got back.

19:02.640 --> 19:06.462
Mmm, just throw it in the safe.
I'll deal with it later.

19:06.970 --> 19:10.758
You know, Ruth, if you need more time,
you take all that you need. I can--

19:10.850 --> 19:12.511
I'm fucking fine, Marty.

19:13.110 --> 19:14.566
Okay? Just...

19:15.480 --> 19:18.779
Just put it in the safe!
I got other shit I have to deal with.

19:25.080 --> 19:26.536
[chattering]

20:02.820 --> 20:05.232
-Call my lavwer.
-I already did.

20:06.830 --> 20:08.400
I want to hear you say it.

20:10.580 --> 20:11.786
Say what?

20:11.870 --> 20:14.828
That we should never have gotten involved
with these people.

20:16.540 --> 20:20.795
Whose idea was it to put the bones
into the poppy field? Ash's?

20:21.880 --> 20:26.044
If I was you, I don't think Ash would be
the topic to be talking about right now.

20:26.140 --> 20:27.255
[Petty] Excuse me.

20:28.600 --> 20:30.056
Here's where I ask
if you'd like to discuss

20:30.140 --> 20:32.222
all your business dealings
with Marty Byrde.

20:32.310 --> 20:34.722
[Jacob] I ain't gonna discuss anything
without a lawyer.

20:34.810 --> 20:36.641
Oh. Well, in that case,
I'm required by law

20:36.730 --> 20:38.766
to tell you that you have the right
to remain silent.

20:38.860 --> 20:42.102
Anything you say can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

20:42.190 --> 20:46.866
The mere existence _of bones_ in a field
does not constitute a crime.

20:46.950 --> 20:48.986
Are you waiving your Miranda rights, hmm?

20:49.580 --> 20:50.729
Will the sheriff please note

20:50.830 --> 20:53.242
that Mr. Snell here is choosing
to waive his Miranda rights?

20:53.750 --> 20:54.785
We're gonna have to bring you in.

20:55.670 --> 20:57.160
On what charge?

20:57.250 --> 21:00.299
There's a county ordinance banning fires,
due to drought.

21:00.380 --> 21:02.007
You're a farmer. You know.

21:02.670 --> 21:03.910
Are you kidding me?

21:04.010 --> 21:05.796
[Petty] The good news is
I'm gonna get that all thrown out

21:05.880 --> 21:07.586
when I charge you for murder.

21:08.100 --> 21:09.044
Cuff him.

21:11.390 --> 21:12.766
Oh, I don't think that's necessary.

21:12.850 --> 21:13.805
I do.

21:14.520 --> 21:15.760
Cuff him.

21:37.210 --> 21:38.370
Let's go.

21:43.300 --> 21:45.666
Would someone please explain
to your business partner

21:45.760 --> 21:49.503
that we need to know exactly what it is
that the FBI is about to uncover.

21:49.590 --> 21:51.342
-Oh, do you now?
-Yes, we do.

21:51.430 --> 21:54.058
Darlene, is Del in that field?

21:54.140 --> 21:55.471
Del...

21:56.770 --> 21:58.476
Del is located elsewhere.

21:59.190 --> 22:00.555
Okay, good.

22:00.650 --> 22:05.349
Uh, and the other missing persons,
are they gonna cause us any problems?

22:05.440 --> 22:06.441
I can't rightly say.

22:06.530 --> 22:08.270
[Helen] In case this is somehow unclear,

22:08.360 --> 22:12.148
targets of murder investigations
are not granted casino licenses.

22:12.240 --> 22:15.903
I don't give a damn
about any casino license.

22:16.000 --> 22:17.149
[Helen] I'll rephrase that.

22:17.250 --> 22:19.491
Your husband might go away
for mass murder.

22:19.580 --> 22:21.070
What do you plan to do about it?

22:21.170 --> 22:24.662
Seems to me
that the people who burnt our field

22:24.760 --> 22:27.160
are the ones who have to come up
with some kind of solution.

22:27.260 --> 22:28.545
But we didn't burn your field.

22:28.630 --> 22:31.508
-[Darlene] You're a goddamn liar.
-I burned the field.

22:32.100 --> 22:33.215
And it's a good thing, too.

22:33.310 --> 22:36.097
Otherwise, both you and Jacob
would be in jail for drug trafficking.

22:43.570 --> 22:45.561
You stood in my home

22:46.610 --> 22:49.647
and talked about adoption agencies.

22:50.860 --> 22:52.521
You lied to me.

22:53.120 --> 22:55.782
I saved this entire enterprise
from going under.

22:57.000 --> 22:59.457
[Marty] Darlene, they found bones
on your property.

22:59.540 --> 23:01.030
We need to find out who they belong to,

23:01.120 --> 23:03.588
and we need to figure out
what to do about it.

23:06.590 --> 23:10.799
You need to get my husband out
of fucking jail.

23:25.900 --> 23:27.310
[machine whirring]

23:32.410 --> 23:33.695
[clears throat]

23:42.210 --> 23:45.031
Pastor, I thought that was you.
What brings you in here?

23:45.130 --> 23:48.588
Uh, on the TV, they said they found bones
on the Snells' property. Is that true?

23:48.670 --> 23:50.251
Yeah. There was a search warrant
executed yesterday.

23:50.340 --> 23:51.216
Is it Grace?

23:51.300 --> 23:52.927
We don't know anything yet.

23:53.510 --> 23:55.671
I told you that they're the ones
that killed her.

23:55.760 --> 23:58.888
Well, we don't want to jump
to any conclusions.

23:58.970 --> 24:01.973
They're in the initial stages
of identifying the remains,

24:02.060 --> 24:04.597
-checking the DNA against missing persons.
-Okay.

24:05.110 --> 24:08.523
But, you know,
I'm afraid Grace isn't in the database.

24:09.780 --> 24:12.351
Um, what ifI bring my boy in?

24:12.450 --> 24:15.738
And you can sample his DNA for Grace.
You can do that, right?

24:16.660 --> 24:19.732
[stammers] Medical examiner's
not gonna be in the office

24:19.830 --> 24:22.993
till the day after tomorrow,
but, yeah, you could bring him back then.

24:23.080 --> 24:24.240
-Okay.
-All right.

24:24.750 --> 24:26.536
-Okay, thank you.
-Sure.

24:40.560 --> 24:42.425
Wendy, that was Darlene.

24:42.520 --> 24:46.763
Mason plans to bring his baby in
to get a sample of Grace's DNA.

24:48.940 --> 24:52.148
-Oh, Jesus. Is Grace in that grave?
-She wouldn't say.

24:53.320 --> 24:56.904
You don't really have a plan
for whatto do about those bones, do you?

24:57.620 --> 24:58.655
Do you?

24:59.450 --> 25:00.439
Uh, not yet.

25:03.370 --> 25:06.419
-I have to talk to Jacob.
-What good will that do?

25:06.500 --> 25:11.085
-Um, honestly, I don't know, but--
-Yeah. No, we have to warn him.

25:13.050 --> 25:15.257
-Who?
-Mason.

25:15.970 --> 25:17.289
You know what Darlene is capable of.

25:17.390 --> 25:19.506
There's no way in hell
she's gonna let him take her down.

25:21.680 --> 25:23.227
I'm right. You know I'm right.

25:29.520 --> 25:32.432
[Jim] I want it on record
that my client is here voluntarily,

25:32.980 --> 25:34.186
as a courtesy.

25:34.900 --> 25:37.107
[Petty clears throat] It's noted.

25:38.740 --> 25:40.696
Okay, let's see.

25:44.290 --> 25:47.612
Fifth largest private business owner
in the state.

25:49.580 --> 25:52.993
And you serve on the boards
of museums, universities.

25:53.090 --> 25:56.582
In the last year,
you donated over $2.3 million

25:56.680 --> 26:00.673
to Republican candidates
in local and state elections.

26:05.810 --> 26:09.769
Guess I understand
what the Byrdes see in you,

26:09.850 --> 26:12.762
but I'm having a hard time understanding
what you see in them.

26:12.860 --> 26:15.988
My client and the Byrdes
have no official business ties.

26:17.400 --> 26:22.690
Does a $50,000 donation to your charity
really buy that much goodwill?

26:23.410 --> 26:25.787
I have nothing but goodwill in this state.

26:26.290 --> 26:30.078
The idea that $50,000 somehow
buys my loyalty is ridiculous.

26:30.540 --> 26:33.748
[Petty] Okay, fine.
